question: What is ComfyUI-PromptOrganizer?
answer: ComfyUI-PromptOrganizer is a custom node for Stable Diffusion ComfyUI that automatically saves AI-generated images to www.txt2any.com.

question: How do you install ComfyUI-PromptOrganizer via terminal?
answer: To install ComfyUI-PromptOrganizer via terminal, open the installation directory under terminal, enter the 'custom_nodes' sub-directory, execute the command 'git clone https://github.com/txt2any/ComfyUI-PromptOrganizer', save the txt2any API Key into the file 'txt2any.ini', and restart ComfyUI.

question: How do you install ComfyUI-PromptOrganizer via ComfyUI Manager?
answer: To install ComfyUI-PromptOrganizer via ComfyUI Manager, first ensure ComfyUI Manager is installed. Then click on the 'Manager' button to bring up the 'ComfyUI Manager Menu' dialog, click on 'Install via Git URL', copy and paste 'https://github.com/txt2any/ComfyUI-PromptOrganizer' into the input field, click 'OK', and restart ComfyUI.

question: How do you configure ComfyUI-PromptOrganizer?
answer: To configure ComfyUI-PromptOrganizer, generate an API Key from your www.txt2any.com account and save it in the file 'txt2any.ini'.

question: How do you use the txt2any Prompt Organizer in ComfyUI?
answer: To use the txt2any Prompt Organizer in ComfyUI, replace the 'Save Image' node with the 'Save image to txt2any' node at the end of your workflow. After executing your workflow and the generation finishes, click on the 'View in txt2any' button to view the image and generation data on the txt2any website.

question: What features are available on www.txt2any.com?
answer: Features available on www.txt2any.com include Prompt Comparison and Generation Data Comparison, which allow you to understand the significance of each text or parameter to achieve better results.

question: Is there a free tier available on www.txt2any.com?
answer: Yes, the free tier on www.txt2any.com will always remain free.
